Polling indicated that the majority of voters support a ceasefire and American mediation in the Gaza war. According to a YouGov poll in March 2024, 52% of Americans supported stopping weapons shipments to Israel, coming largely from Americans who voted for Biden in 2020 (62% support) and people who did not vote in 2020 (60%). Republicans opposed halting weapons shipments by 25 points. Republicans generally supported arms to Israel, while Democrats were divided on the issue.

{{Jill Stein series}}
{{main|2024 Green Party presidential primaries|2024 Green National Convention|Jill Stein 2024 presidential campaign}}
The party's nominee in Jill Stein 2012 presidential campaign|2012 and Jill Stein 2016 presidential campaign|2016, Stein is a physician and a former member of the Lexington, Massachusetts|Lexington Representative town meeting|Town Meeting. On August 16, Stein selected academic Butch Ware as her running mate. Stein achieved ballot access in 38 states, and was eligible to receive write-in votes in seven states. She was not eligible to receive write-in votes in the remaining states or the District of Columbia.

